text: The humerus is the upper forearm bone in tetrapods. It connects to the shoulder blade (scapula) at the upper end, and the elbow below. ==Images== File:Gray326.png|Attachment at the shoulder File:AnteriorHeadOfLeftHumerus.jpg|Left humerus head File:MedialHeadOfLeftHumerus.jpg|Left humerus head, from other side File:MedialHumerusRadiusUlnaArticulated.jpg|Left humerus at the elbow File:LateralLeftHumerusRadiusUlnaArticulated.jpg|Ellbow, other side File:LeftHumanPosteriorDistalHumerusExtended.jpg|Elbow, stretched Category:Bones
